Sentencas: Ce0.85Sm0.15O1.925 (SDC) and Ce0.85Sm0.15O1.925-0.5 at.% NiO (SDCN) are investigated as electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Effects of NiO on the conductivity of Ce0.85Sm0.15O1.925 and on electrochemical properties of the cathode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: Impedance spectroscopy measurements reveal that the grain boundary resistance can be significantly reduced by adding 0.5 at.% NiO to SDC.
Titulo: Effects of NiO on the conductivity of Ce0.85Sm0.15O1.925 and on electrochemical properties of the cathode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: Symmetric cells of the BaCo0.7Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-delta (BCFN) electrode on SDC and SDCN electrolytes are fabricated and the electrochemical properties of the electrode/electrolyte interface are investigated.
Titulo: Effects of NiO on the conductivity of Ce0.85Sm0.15O1.925 and on electrochemical properties of the cathode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of the BCFN electrode on the SDCN electrolyte is much lower than that of the BCFN electrode on the SDC electrolyte, mainly because of the increase in the electrolyte conductivity and the decrease in the Si content at the electrode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Effects of NiO on the conductivity of Ce0.85Sm0.15O1.925 and on electrochemical properties of the cathode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: NiO is able to restrict the diffusion of the siliceous impurity from the electrolyte to the electrode/electrolyte interface.
Titulo: Effects of NiO on the conductivity of Ce0.85Sm0.15O1.925 and on electrochemical properties of the cathode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: Single cells based on SDC and SDCN electrolytes are fabricated using Ni0.9Cu0.1Ox-SDC as the anode and BCFN as the cathode.
Titulo: Effects of NiO on the conductivity of Ce0.85Sm0.15O1.925 and on electrochemical properties of the cathode/electrolyte interface

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, the maximum power density of the SDCN-based cell is 0.745 W cm(-2), which is much higher than that of the SDC-based cell.
Titulo: Effects of NiO on the conductivity of Ce0.85Sm0.15O1.925 and on electrochemical properties of the cathode/electrolyte interface
